George Odiwuor @PeopleDailyKe Up to 11,000 small-scale women traders in Homa Bay have begun benefiting from a Sh15.1 million grant from the office of Woman Rep Gladys Wanga. On Sunday, Wanga  launched the initiative to enable small-scale traders to boost their businesses. Women traders from 80 markets in the county are set to benefit Speaking at Sofia market in Homa Bay town where she distributed the funds, Wanga said  the distribution will go on until next year. “I will personally go to every market that is expected to benefit to oversee the distribution of the funds so as to ensure the intended people receive the money,” she said. Transform lives Women traders  welcomed the initiative saying it will transform their lives. Jane Anyango, a trader at Sofia Market said she will use the funds to get more stock for her business.